text.section:
A custom home builder may make withdrawals from an escrow account established in compliance with subsection (a)(1) of this section solely for the purpose of:
Returning all or a portion of the sum of money to the buyer;
Paying documented claims of persons who have furnished labor or material, including fuel, according to the draw schedule in the custom home contract for which the funds were advanced;
Paying a sum of money to the custom home builder if the buyer forfeits the sum under the terms of the contract of sale; or
Final payment upon the issuance of an occupancy permit or possession.
